5000|$|While {{defending}} the Chicago Seven, Kunstler put {{the war in}} Vietnam on trial—asking Judy Collins to sing [...] "Where Have All The Flowers Gone" [...] from <b>the</b> <b>witness</b> <b>stand,</b> placing a Viet Congflag <b>on</b> <b>the</b> defence table, and wearing a black armband to commemorate the war dead. Ron Kuby, in his 1995 eulogy of Kunstler.|$|R
