2500|$|Note: In hearsay law, [...] "witness" [...] means {{someone who}} testifies under oath, from <b>the</b> <b>witness</b> <b>stand</b> and [...] "declarant" [...] refers {{to someone who}} makes a {{statement}} of any kind, whether or not under oath, and whether {{in or out of}} court (according to the Federal Rules of Evidence).|$|R
